  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN188.2-kilavi">iraviṟ ciṟaippuṟamākat tōḻi colliyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">What the confidante said at night when [HE] was behind the hedge.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="AN188.2">
        <l>peruṅkaṭaṉ mukanta palkiḷaik koṇmū</l>
        <l>viruṇṭuyar vicumpiṉ valaṉērpu vaḷaiip</l>
        <l>pōrppuṟu muraci ṉiraṅki muṟaipurin</l>
        <l>taṟaneṟi piḻaiyāt tiṟaṉaṟi maṉṉa</l>
        <l>raruñcamat tetirnta peruñkai yāṭavar</l>
        <l>kaḻitteṟi vāḷi ṉaḻippiṉa viḷaṅku</l>
        <l>miṉṉuṭaik karuviyai yāki nāḷuṅ</l>
        <l>koṉṉē ceytiyō vara<supplied>va</supplied>m poṉṉeṉa</l>
        <l>malarnta vēṅkai malitoṭa raṭaiccip</l>
        <l>polinta vāyamoṭu kāṇṭaka viyalit</l>
        <l>taḻalai vāṅkiyun taṭṭai yōcciyu</l>
        <l>maḻalēr ceyalai yantaḻai <supplied>tai</supplied>iyuṅ</l>
        <l>kuṟamakaḷ kākku mēṉaṟ</l>
        <l>puṟa<supplied>muṟa</supplied> tarutiyō vāḻiya maḻaiyē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>As clouds with many relatives that drew from the great sea (1)</l>
        <l>rise clockwise [and] enclose the darkened high sky, (2)</l>
        <l>sounding like covered drums, keeping in order(?), (3)</l>
        <l>you, being a accumulation endowed with flashes (7a-c)</l>
        <l>that shine as destructors, like the swords stripped [and] swung (6)</l>
        <l>by men with big hands that opposed in difficult battle (5)</l>
        <l>kings who know the unfailing elements in the path of duty, (4)</l>
        <l>will you futilely make noise all day? (7d-8c)</l>
        <l>The millet that is guarded by the hillman’s daughter, (13)</l>
        <l>while inserting [flowers] into bindings abounding in kino that blossoms like gold, (8df.)</l>
        <l>moving forward fit to be seen with [her] flourishing companions, (10)</l>
        <l>striking Taḻals and raising Taṭṭai [rods], (11)</l>
        <l>and weaving [skirts of] the pretty foliage of the fire-like Aśoka, (12)</l>
        <l>will you bring [it] out, may you live, rain? (14)</l>
      </lg>
        </div>
